<div id="review_2512322636" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2512322636" />
    <a title="Cinda" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1258344-cinda"><img alt="Cinda" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1638240892p2/1258344.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2512322636?book_show_action=true">Sep 10, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Cinda" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Cinda" href="/user/show/1258344-cinda">Cinda</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1258344-cinda?shelf=adult">adult</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1258344-cinda?shelf=nonfiction">nonfiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1258344-cinda?shelf=history">history</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1258344-cinda?shelf=revwar">revwar</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1258344-cinda?shelf=biography">biography</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2512322636" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14712628699388604806">I&apos;ve been feasting on history lately, with this the latest course. At 817 pages, this book isn&apos;t for everyone, but having read Chernow&apos;s Hamilton, Vidal&apos;s Burr, Gordon-Reed&apos;s The Hemingses of Monticello, Ambrose&apos;s Undaunted Courage, I chose to fill in this chasm in my knowledge of the early republic. As always, the truth is more complex and nuanced than legend. People who claim to love this country should invest more time in the study of its history. </span>
  <span id="freeText14712628699388604806" style="display:none">I've been feasting on history lately, with this the latest course. At 817 pages, this book isn't for everyone, but having read Chernow's Hamilton, Vidal's Burr, Gordon-Reed's The Hemingses of Monticello, Ambrose's Undaunted Courage, I chose to fill in this chasm in my knowledge of the early republic. As always, the truth is more complex and nuanced than legend. People who claim to love this country should invest more time in the study of its history. </span>
  <a data-text-id="14712628699388604806" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
