  <img src="https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1416071998ra/11884885.gif" alt="" class="gr-hostedUserImg">
</a><br> <br>While <em>
  <strong>Chernow</strong>
</em> gives dimension and complexity to Washington's character and leadership, it doesn't come across as an attempt to smear a whitewashed vision of Washington that has been passed down through history. I found my opinions of and about Washington evolving with his own perceptions of the world. Though, obviously I didn't start off with Washington thinking that one should pick a slave with good teeth (ironic given his dental situation).<br> <br>Long of the short, this book is pretty revolutionary (see what I did there?)<br><br> </span>
