<div id="review_369481791" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/369481791" />
    <a title="David" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/10835551-david"><img alt="David" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1362102968p2/10835551.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/369481791?book_show_action=true">Jul 15, 2012</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="David" class="user" itemprop="url" name="David" href="/user/show/10835551-david">David</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/9042669-washington">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer369481791" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17896530807034233971">Considering that authors have written 60 volume biographies on George Washington, this was a fascinating condensed version at over 900 pages. Loaded with facts about his early childhood and family interactions that built his character. No &quot;chopped down the cherry tree&quot; made up myths. It was very thoroughly researched and draws on many previous works by other qualified experts and authors. It also continues his life story through his two terms as president followed by a too short retirement until</span>
  <span id="freeText17896530807034233971" style="display:none">Considering that authors have written 60 volume biographies on George Washington, this was a fascinating condensed version at over 900 pages. Loaded with facts about his early childhood and family interactions that built his character. No "chopped down the cherry tree" made up myths. It was very thoroughly researched and draws on many previous works by other qualified experts and authors. It also continues his life story through his two terms as president followed by a too short retirement until his death in December 1799. Most of what I knew consisted of his being Commander-In-Chief of the American Colonial Army and that he was President. This book lets you really get to know George Washington as an insecure man who always regretted not being as educated as most of the other Founding Fathers. But he brought qualities that made him the unanimous choice by others to lead the army and then the nation. A very long read but well worth it.</span>
  <a data-text-id="17896530807034233971" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


